description.plain:
Initially coming up as a lyrical rapper before crossing over into pop realms and making a switch to pop punk, a shift that led to Billboard dubbing him the “Crown Prince of Pop Punk”, Machine Gun Kelly (born Colson Baker) is an American rapper, singer, songwriter, and actor from Cleveland, Ohio.

Traveling the world because of his parents’ jobs before settling down in Cleveland, Machine Gun Kelly, commonly referred to as MGK, earned his stage name for his lightning-fast delivery while still in high school. His breakthrough came at the start of the 2010s with his party-rap hit “Wild Boy”, mixing his lightning-fast flow with hedonistic, party-ready lyrics over a bass-heavy beat. He would go on to release two more rap albums before making his crossover into pop.

His third album, bloom, marked a stylistic and commercial turning point for the Ohio rapper. Led by his smash hit single “Bad Things”, a pop-rap duet with, at-the-time, rising songstress Camila Cabello, the album saw his style pivot to pop and his sales increase accordingly. With “Bad Things” becoming a top five hit on the Hot 100 and reaching the top spot of the pop charts, as well as the album’s other hit, “At My Best”, nearly cracking the top 20 of the pop charts, the album became the most successful of Machine Gun Kelly’s career.

After a highly-publicized feud with Eminem and a critically-acclaimed rap-rock album in 2018 and 2019, respectively, Machine Gun Kelly started to become a household name in 2020 with the release of Tickets To My Downfall, reviving pop punk with a uniquely hip-hop-inspired spin. The approach proved successful, with the album’s single my ex’s best friend” staying on the Hot 100 chart for a full year. At the front of a revival of pop-punk and rock music in the mainstream, he followed up with 2022’s mainstream sellout, for which he earned a Grammy nomination, a first in his career.

To date, Machine Gun Kelly has certified sales of 25 million singles and 2.5 million albums.

songs.full_title: RAP DEVIL by Machine Gun Kelly
songs.title: RAP DEVIL

description.plain:
Machine Gun Kelly released this track as a response to Eminem’s disses from his surprise 2018 album, Kamikaze. On “Not Alike,” Em raps:

He wants to keep up his tough demeanor
So he does a feature, decides to team up with Nina
But next time you don’t gotta use Tech N9ne
If you wanna come at me with a sub, Machine Gun
And I’m talkin' to you, but you already know who the fuck you are, Kelly
I don’t use sublims and sure as fuck don’t sneak-diss
But keep commenting on my daughter Hailie[…]

Eminem also name-dropped Kelly on the first track of Kamikaze, “The Ringer,” rhyming MGK’s name with Iggy Azalea’s, another artist he has beef with. The name-drop is included in a line mocking the flow of Lil Pump’s hit song “Gucci Gang”:

So finger-bang, chicken wang, MGK, Iggy ‘zae
Lil Pump, Lil Xan imitate Lil Wayne
I should aim at everybody in the game, pick a name

The title “RAP DEVIL” is a play on “Rap God,” Em’s 2013 single that was a major success and considered by many to be a lyrical masterpiece.

Eminem released his response, “KILLSHOT,” on September 14, 2018, eleven days after this song’s release.

songs.full_title: DAYWALKER! by Machine Gun Kelly (Ft. CORPSE)
songs.title: DAYWALKER!

description.plain:
“DAYWALKER!” marks the first collaboration between singer/rapper Machine Gun Kelly, and content-creator-turned-rapper CORPSE. The track is CORPSE’s first major collab since the release of his breakthrough singles “E-GIRLS ARE RUINING MY LIFE!” and “agoraphobic”.

In supernatural fantasy, a ‘daywalker’ is a vampire that can walk in sunlight unaffected. They can sustain extended periods in sunlight and even has traces of a soul. Usually, vampires burn under sunlight and are known primarily as ‘nightcrawlers’. A more well-known version of the daywalker is the Marvel Comics character Blade.

Since December 2020, both CORPSE and MGK had been teasing an upcoming collaboration during live streams and via brief snippets on Twitter, but the song’s full reveal came on March 9th, when both artists posted the song’s cover art to social media.

The song serves as a return to form for Machine Gun Kelly, after the success of his #1 pop-punk album Tickets To My Downfall, while still allowing him to branch into new directions as he fuses his own rock sound with CORPSE’s signature style of horror-core rap.

A music video for the track dropped on March 18th.
Since CORPSE has not done an official face-reveal, his lines were performed and lip-synched by fellow
YouTuber/streamer VALKYRAE.

songs.title: ​bloody valentine

description.plain:
“Bloody Valentine” sees MGK hoping for something real with a lover, taking a noticeable departure from the wary attitude he possessed about betrayal on 2019’s Hotel Diablo. He announced the song via Twitter on April 27th, 2020, calling it the “first single” from Tickets To My Downfall.

The music video for the single was released on May 20th starring American actress Megan Fox and amassed over twenty million views within its first month. Machine Gun Kelly would also go on to appear to confirm a relationship with Fox roughly a month after the video’s release.

The song debuted atop the Billboard Rock Digital Songs chart, eventually achieving massive commercial success and reaching #50 on the Billboard Hot 100 and #51 on the UK Singles chart.
